{% block content %}

<div class="govuk-grid-row">
  <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">

    <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">
      Having your say about a national infrastructure project 
    </h1>
    <p>This guide is for individuals and organisations who want to have their say about a project. The overall process is called the <a href="../dco-process-guide/index.html">Development Consent Order (DCO) process</a>. A developer submits their application to the Planning Inspectorate and we examine the project and make a recommendation to the Secretary of State about if the project should go ahead.</p>
    <p>As part of this process, members of the public, organisations and people acting on behalf of others can have their say about the project and tell us why they think it should or should not go ahead.</p>

    <div id="step-by-step-navigation" class="app-step-nav app-step-nav--large app-step-nav--active" data-show-text="Show" data-hide-text="Hide" data-show-all-text="Show all" data-hide-all-text="Hide all">
